#. type: Title ==
#: pcbnew_introduction.adoc:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Introduction to Pcbnew"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pcbnew_introduction.adoc:4
#, no-wrap
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pcbnew_introduction.adoc:10
msgid ""
"Pcbnew is a powerful printed circuit board software tool available for the Linux, Microsoft Windows and "
"Apple OS X operating systems.  Pcbnew is used in association with the schematic capture program Eeschema "
"to create printed circuit boards."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pcbnew_introduction.adoc:17
msgid ""
"Pcbnew manages libraries of footprints. Each footprint is a drawing of the physical component including "
"its land pattern (the layout of pads on the circuit board). The required footprints are automatically "
"loaded during the reading of the Netlist. Any changes to footprint selection or annotation can be "
"changed in the schematic and updated in pcbnew by regenerating the netlist and reading it in pcbnew "
"again."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pcbnew_introduction.adoc:22
msgid ""
"Pcbnew provides a design rules check (DRC) tool which prevents track and pad clearance issues as well as "
"preventing nets from being connected that aren't connected in the netlist/schematic. When using the "
"interactive router it continuously runs the design rules check and will help automatically route "
"individual traces."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pcbnew_introduction.adoc:26
msgid ""
"Pcbnew provides a rats nest display, a hairline connecting the pads of footprints which are connected on "
"the schematic. These connections move dynamically as track and footprint movements are made."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pcbnew_introduction.adoc:30
msgid ""
"Pcbnew has a simple but effective autorouter to assist in the production of the circuit board. An Export/"
"Import in SPECCTRA dsn format allows the use of more advanced auto-routers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pcbnew_introduction.adoc:34
msgid ""
"Pcbnew provides options specifically provided for the production of ultra high frequency microwave "
"circuits (such as pads of trapezoidal and complex form, automatic layout of coils on the printed "
"circuit, etc)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pcbnew_introduction.adoc:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "Principal design features"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pcbnew_introduction.adoc:39
msgid "The smallest unit in pcbnew is 1 nanometer. All dimensions are stored as integer nanometers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pcbnew_introduction.adoc:44
msgid ""
"Pcbnew can generate up to 32 layers of copper, 14 technical layers (silk screen, solder mask, component "
"adhesive, solder paste and edge cuts) plus 4 auxiliary layers (drawings and comments) and manages in "
"real time the hairline indication (rats nest) of missing tracks."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pcbnew_introduction.adoc:47
msgid "The display of the PCB elements (tracks, pads, text, drawings...)  is customizable:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pcbnew_introduction.adoc:49
msgid "In full or outline."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pcbnew_introduction.adoc:50
msgid "With or without track clearance."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pcbnew_introduction.adoc:54
msgid ""
"For complex circuits, the display of layers, zones, and components can be hidden in a selective way for "
"clarity on screen. Nets of traces can be highlighted to provide high contrast as well."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pcbnew_introduction.adoc:56
msgid "Footprints can be rotated to any angle, with a resolution of 0.1 degree."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pcbnew_introduction.adoc:59
msgid ""
"Pcbnew includes a Footprint Editor that allows editing of individual footprints that have been on a pcb "
"or editing a footprint in a library."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pcbnew_introduction.adoc:61
msgid "The Footprint Editor provides many time saving tools such as:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pcbnew_introduction.adoc:64
msgid "Fast pad numbering by simply dragging the mouse over pads in the order you want them numbered."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pcbnew_introduction.adoc:66
msgid "Easy generation of rectangular and circular arrays of pads for LGA/BGA or circular footprints."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pcbnew_introduction.adoc:67
msgid "Semi-automatic aligning of rows or columns of pads."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pcbnew_introduction.adoc:74
msgid ""
"Footprint pads have a variety of properties that can be adjusted. The pads can be round, rectangular, "
"oval or trapezoidal. For through-hole parts drills can be offset inside the pad and be round or a slot. "
"Individual pads can also be rotated and have unique soldermask, net, or paste clearance. Pads can also "
"have a solid connection or a thermal relief connection for easier manufacturing. Any combination of "
"unique pads can be placed within a footprint."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pcbnew_introduction.adoc:77
msgid "Pcbnew easily generates all the documents necessary for production:"
